The policemen, who shot an unarmed suspect dead in Lagos has been revealed. A viral video of a restrained man shot to death by two policemen had generated outrage on social media, with Nigerians calling for the prosecution of the officers. The policemen were identified as Fabiyi Omomayara, Olaniyi Solomon, Solomon Sunday and Aliyu Mukaila. They were attached to Iba Division Patrol team. The Nigeria Police Force apprehended the four personnel and said they would be charged for murder. It was also revealed that the incident happened on Monday at about 3.00pm.



